reviews.headline: Patchy and Dry
reviews.comments: I have oily skin and this was still dry on my skin, patchy when trying blend. People always say "maybe you're using the wrong primer" I tried it with a water based primer and another time with just lotion. It still dried and got patchy. I always blend my concealer with my finger for a more natural look so the product really shouldn't be picking up the way it does.

reviews.headline: I would not buy this again, does not live up to Mac quality
reviews.comments: I dont know why Mac is making so many changes to their line.  I have been using Mac product for over 15 years and cant even find my regular product anymore.  Tried this product and it made me break out which never happens when I use Mac product.

reviews.headline: WOW
reviews.comments: I love the foundation version of this product and was really excited to see the concealer come out and WOW my expectations were blown away! I'm 31 woth few lines but very delicate under eye skin and this looks amazing! Light skin like texture, great coverage! Hydrating and you need just a little dot! Hols up all day and never dries out my under eyes! I'm absolutely in love…in my opinion this is better than Nars and Natasha concealers!

reviews.headline: Not luminous or hydrating
reviews.comments: I bought this because i seen all the good reviews. I usually let my concealer set for 1-2 minutes so i can get the best coverage but when it was time to blend it in, it didnt budge. It was sooooo dry. Im not sure if it was the skin prep but i want to love this so bad so i will give it anothet try. Otherwise, im returning it.

reviews.headline: Am I the only one....
reviews.comments: I wanted to love this but it dried down matte and cakey. I have dry undereyes to begin with and it just didnt work. It dried down so dry that my undereye was tight and you could see all my lines. I tried it with several fave undereye creams but no success. Also, the color leaned more yellow than neutral and oxicide a little. This one was a no go for me.

reviews.headline: I love this too much
reviews.comments: Okay so let me just start out by saying I like to use concealer all over my face. Instead of using a foundation or skin tint I like to cover my face in elf halo glow liquid filter and then go in with a concealer where I want a little coverage then just blend everything out together. I have used so many concealers and this one is the best! All you need is a little bit. On my skin it blends in so beautifully and creates a skin that looks better than mine and not cakey, the texture to me feels light weight and hydrating. of course too much of anything will look cakey and textured. the glow it also gives is beautiful. It also looks great under my eyes very smooth.  I set my face with the covergirl advanced radiance compact and my oh my it's a dream team on my skin.  it is expensive but I can definitely tell a difference when I use this compared to my drugstore concealer. it lasts all day on my face and didn't break up any of the products I put on top. I am obsessed. it does break up around my nose throughout the day but everything does because I have allergies..uggh.

faceoff_positive.comments:
This concealer is unique in comparison to all other concealers I've ever tried. 
The packaging is absolutely luxurious. It feels heavy, the gold details are amazing. The applicator is a rounded doe foot, it's very soft and fits in small contours easily. 
The formula is very runny and liquidy. It's more of a water serum than a cream. Because of the thin texture, it blends like a dream. It takes no effort to blend and the result looks like a filter has been applied. It's buildable, so with one layer, redness is reduced and darkness is brightened. With two layers, it covers blemishes and my under eye circles. The color matches my skin so perfectly that I can spot conceal without it looking patchy without needing foundation to even everything out. It looks like I have no makeup on at all. It just looks like my skin but better. Everything about it feels like skincare as opposed to makeup, even the ingredients are mainly skincare. The packaging is opaque for the purpose of protecting the vitamin c, which I appreciate. It's unscented to minimize irritation. My skin didn't have any negative reaction to the concealer. 

It sits beautifully on my skin. It doesn't make pores look larger, doesn't make me shiny. It has a very natural skin like finish.  

When trying it, I didn't use powder to set. I did experience creasing on my eyes, which is normal for me, but I also had creasing between my eyebrows. It accentuated some dryness around my chin in a few places. I had to mess around with my skincare products prior to application, and also make sure to wait for my skincare to fully absorb or else I experienced pilling. I found if I used less skincare, so only moisturizer first, reduced pilling. If I used my normal serums underneath my moisturizer and then applied the concealer, it would pill up and fall off. I'm sure if applied to bare skin there would be zero issue, but I'm not willing to forgo my skincare. Using a damp sponge helped reduce texture.
faceoff_positive.headline: Amazing for a no makeup look

faceoff_negative.comments:
*I received this product from Mac in exchange for a review (thank you!)* The things I look for in a concealer are coverage, and moisturizing ability. My under eyes are dark (I'm Arab) and tend to be on the dry side. This product comes in a sleek, luxurious tube. It has a traditional chubby doe foot applicator. This concealer also contains skincare as it claims to diminish the look of dark circles over time (that's always a plus). 

I liked that the concealer is medium coverage and very liquidy, I don't like heavy gloopy concealers. I don't usually wear foundation so I applied it over my skincare and tried both a beauty blender and a brush under either eye. I also tried on spots on my skin where I wanted to highlight and where I wanted to conceal. Under my eyes it left a white/grey cast and really picked up on my dry spots. But it did a great job highlighting my forehead and covering a red pimple I had. 

Overall I wouldn't say this concealer is unique. I think it might be best suited for people with mild under eye circles, red under eyes and normal to oily skin. I loved the consistency and ability to blend well. And I love that it is buildable.
faceoff_negative.headline: Light and buildable concealer for specific skin types
